ll enjoy&#8230;</a></li><li><a class="kb-table-of-contents__entry" href="#Did_you_make_it?">Did you make it?</a></li></ul></div></nav></div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-group has-theme-palette-8-background-color has-background is-vertical is-layout-flex wp-container-core-group-is-layout-8cf370e7 wp-block-group-is-layout-flex">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">WHY YOU&#8217;LL LOVE THIS</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Incredibly crispy</strong> – rolling each potato in parmesan before roasting creates a golden, almost crunchy crust that you just can&#8217;t get any other way </li>



<li><strong>Simple ingredients</strong> – olive oil, garlic, Italian seasoning, parmesan. That&#8217;s really it!</li>



<li><strong>Perfect BBQ side dish</strong> – holds up well and looks beautiful on a table </li>



<li><strong>Ready in 40 minutes</strong> – mostly hands-off oven time, minimal effort</li>
</ul>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-group is-vertical is-layout-flex wp-container-core-group-is-layout-8cf370e7 wp-block-group-is-layout-flex">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-large-font-size" style="text-transform:uppercase">WHAT ARE CRISPY GARLIC PARMESAN POTATOES?</h2>



<p>Crispy garlic parmesan potatoes are baby potatoes that are halved, boiled until tender, then coated in garlic and Italian seasoning. Then each potato is rolled in finely grated parmesan and roasted cut-side down at high heat until golden and crispy. The parmesan forms a crust directly on the potato (yes, an actual crust!).</p>



<p>It&#8217;s a simple idea done really well. The kind of recipe that looks like it requires more effort than it does, which is exactly why it works so well for BBQs and gatherings.</p>



<p>My version serves them with a fresh herb dip on the side, which cuts through the richness beautifully. You don&#8217;t need much, the potatoes are the star here.</p>
</div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-image">
<figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="683" height="1024" src="https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-5-683x1024.jpg" alt="crispy garlic parmesan potatoes with yogurt dip" class="wp-image-4345" style="width:683px;height:auto" srcset="https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-5-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-5-200x300.jpg 200w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-5-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-5-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-5-750x1125.jpg 750w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-5-600x900.jpg 600w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-5.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" /></figure>
</div>


<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">FOOD SCIENCE NOTES</h2>



<p>Boiling the potatoes first is not an extra step, it&#8217;s the whole reason these work. The inside is already fully cooked before the oven turns on, so the high heat can do one job and one job only: make the outside as crispy as possible.</p>



<p>And please, let them steam dry after draining. I know it feels like nothing but wet potatoes go into the oven wet and come out&#8230; wet. Two minutes on the counter changes everything.</p>
</div></div>
</div></div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-large-font-size">HOW TO MAKE IT</h2>



<p class="has-theme-palette-1-background-color has-background has-small-font-size"><em><strong>Please note:</strong></em>&nbsp;<em>This is just an overview – the full ingredients and directions are in the recipe card at the bottom of this post.</em></p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 1: Boil the potatoes</strong> </h3>



<p>Place the halved baby potatoes in a pot of well-salted water. Bring to a boil and cook for about 8 minutes, until just fork-tender (you don&#8217;t want them falling apart). Drain well and let them sit in the colander for a few minutes to steam dry.</p>


<div class="wp-block-image">
<figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="683" height="1024" src="https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-683x1024.jpg" alt="potatoes in a pot" class="wp-image-4346" srcset="https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-200x300.jpg 200w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-750x1125.jpg 750w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-600x900.jpg 600w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" /></figure>
</div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 2: Season</strong> </h3>



<p>Transfer the potatoes to a large bowl. Add olive oil, minced garlic, Italian seasoning, salt, and black pepper. Toss until every piece is well coated.</p>


<div class="wp-block-image">
<figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="683" height="1024" src="https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-2-683x1024.jpg" alt="potatoes in a bowl with seasoninga" class="wp-image-4347" srcset="https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-2-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-2-200x300.jpg 200w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-2-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-2-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-2-750x1125.jpg 750w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-2-600x900.jpg 600w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-2.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" /></figure>
</div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 3: Coat with parmesan</strong> </h3>



<p>Spread the finely grated parmesan on a flat plate. Roll each potato piece in the parmesan, pressing lightly so it sticks on all sides. The more it sticks, the better the crust.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 4: Arrange and roast</strong> </h3>



<p>Place the potatoes cut-side down on a lined baking sheet. Roast at 220°C (425°F) for 25–30 minutes, until deeply golden and crispy. Don&#8217;t move them around and let the crust form undisturbed.</p>
</div></div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-image">
<figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="683" height="1024" src="https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-3-683x1024.jpg" alt="potatoes covered in parmesan on a tray" class="wp-image-4348" srcset="https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-3-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-3-200x300.jpg 200w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-3-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-3-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-3-750x1125.jpg 750w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-3-600x900.jpg 600w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-3.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" /></figure>
</div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 5: Finish and serve</strong> </h3>



<p>Transfer to a serving plate, sprinkle with fresh parsley, and serve with a homemade fresh herb dip on the side.</p>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">STORING AND REHEATING</h2>



<p id="STORING_AND_FREEZING_TIPS">These crispy garlic parmesan potatoes keeps in the fridge for up to 3 days in an airtight container. They lose their crunch overnight. To bring it back, reheat in the oven at 200°C for 8–10 minutes. For a BBQ, these are honestly best made fresh. They only take 40 minutes and the difference is noticeable.</p>
</div></div>
</div></div>
</div></div>



<div style="height:0px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-group has-theme-palette-8-background-color has-background"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-large-font-size">NOTES FROM MY KITCHEN</h2>



<p>I&#8217;ve been making a version of these crispy garlic parmesan potatoes for years. And for years, I was doing it wrong (or not wrong exactly, but not <em>right</em> either). I used to toss the parmesan in with the oil and seasonings, mix everything together, and call it done. They were delicious. But never quite crispy enough, and I could never figure out why.</p>



<p>Then one day I thought &#8211; what if I roll each potato in the parmesan separately instead? Press it in, let it stick properly, give it a real chance to form a crust. So I did. And that was it. That one small change is the whole reason this recipe is what it is now.</p>



<p>Use finely grated parmesan, not the coarse stuff. It sticks better and crisps more evenly. And don&#8217;t rush the rolling step. It takes a couple of extra minutes but that&#8217;s where the magic actually happens.</p>
</div></div>


<div class="wp-block-image">
<figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="683" height="1024" src="https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-9-683x1024.jpg" alt="crispy garlic parmesan potatoes with yogurt dip" class="wp-image-4349" srcset="https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-9-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-9-200x300.jpg 200w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-9-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-9-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-9-750x1125.jpg 750w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-9-600x900.jpg 600w, https://goodfooddiscoveries.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/crispy-garlic-parmesan-potatoes-9.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" /></figure>
</div>


